d valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Overcoming artist block and just plain STARTING.</span><hr size=1> HELP!<br>
<br>
I started drawing a number of years ago after coming onto the book &quot;Drawing on the Right Side of the Brain&quot; but so far, all my artwork has been what I call &quot;sight&quot; drawing - that is, copying from another piece of artwork or a photo (and I must say, I can do a fairly decent job at that part).<br>
<br>
One thing I am TOTALLY stuck on, though is how the heck to start drawing &quot;creative&quot; characters and stuff like the stuff in the gallery here (or anywhere else for that matter).<br>
<br>
SO - can anyone offer some advice on how to actually get started &quot;creating&quot; drawings instead of simply just &quot;copying&quot; them? ALL MY CREATIVE STUFF LOOKS LIKE CRAP. (How does one progress?)<br>
<br>
HELP!<br>
<br>
(Thanks.) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uevnhnssn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>evn hnssn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/26/01 2:25:38 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www16.brinkster.com/evnhnssn/evnezp.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Overcoming artist block and just plain STARTING.</span><hr size=1> use the methods that are common to this board:<br>
<br>
01. stick figure<br>
02. ball and cone<br>
03. scribbling<br>
04. doodle <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
05. sketch (you can always erase a sketch!)<br>
<br>
i do not recall any more methods, and they seem to define themselves... so i would not go through the pains in explaining the processes. sorry!<br>
<br>
just remember to 'flesh' and remember to use 'guidelines' to figure proportions. use reference pictures to guide you, too.<br>
<br>
.evn. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ukismetone.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kismetone</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/26/01 11:41:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Overcoming artist block and just plain STARTING.</span><hr size=1> What interested you? Start there... <br>
<br>
Do you like the great outdoors? Do you like Manga? Do you like Mecha? Do you like puppies and kittens?  All my best work is inspired by drawing the things I am interested in. Whether it's Monkeys or Kung Fu or both. <br>
<br>
Picture what you want to draw. Now, sit down and draw. You can use references but try not to copy. For example if I'm working on mecha I'll have pictures of machines and engine parts lying around but not the exact mecha I'm drawing.<br>
<br>
Or another exercise would be to find a picture you like and try and draw the same thing from another angle. Just do whatever works for you.... exercise your creativity.<br>
<br>
-kismetONE<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.kismetONE.com">www.kismetONE.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.MonkeyFu.com">www.MonkeyFu.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/udrowtales.showPublicProfile?language=EN>drowtales</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/26/01 12:29:16 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.drowtales.com/kern.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Overcoming artist block and just plain STARTING.</span><hr size=1> Hum, here my suggestion, call some friends, play a roleplaying game, and this way you get plenty of original idea by combining the fantasy of many persons ^_^.<br>
I suggest ad&amp;d.<br>
<br>
Trought watching some anime and reading manga may help of course...but it not completly original by doing so....better then nothing trought. Lot of manga have &quot;sketch&quot; section at the end(like the one i buyed today,  battle angel alita) who help you finding idea of pose and stuff like that.<br>
 <p>Chibi are tasty! ^_^
<br>
<a href="http://www.drowtales.com" target="_blank"><IMG SRC="http://www.drowtales.com/links/cds_banner.JPG" BORDER=0 WIDTH=468 HEIGHT=60></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ukennygeeze.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kenny Geeze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/27/01 12:03:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Overcoming artist block and just plain STARTING.</span><hr size=1> Well, you may not like to copy, but that's exactly what you might have to do. Get your hands on some comic books or just some pics off the internet and copy/trace them relentlessly. Drawing a character once and then moving on isn't enough. Draw them five or six times. Then throw the print-out away and try your best to draw it from memory. Fill in the parts you don't remember with some freehand stuff. Or find data from another picture and get data from that.<br>
Eventually your own style will develope and you'll be able to start some freehand stuff. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/urtagent5.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rtagent5</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/27/01 7:05:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Overcoming artist block and just plain STARTING.</span><hr size=1> Play a lot of rpgs and fighting games, watch a lot of anime, read a lot of manga, it'll work, believe me, it works<br>
<br>
good luck <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uscadpaulg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>scadpaulg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/27/01 7:58:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Overcoming artist block and just plain STARTIN</span><hr size=1> Thanks, all.<br>
<br>
Your advice is all helpful. I tend to forget that I'm still a beginner and it's like I want to cross the Grand Canyon in one fell swoop, but I know it doesn't work that way. (It just sucks because it takes so much time to get good!)<br>
<br>
So - I'll just start slowly, copying and stuff, which I can do - but I was just wondering how to &quot;branch off&quot; from that...<br>
<br>
The comment about doing a drawing 5 or 6 times makes sense.<br>
<br>
I'm just afraid of doing crappy work, you know?<br>
<br>
(Thanks again, everyone...)<br>
<br>
Oh - and why the suggestions to play rpg? I haven't played in a long time. Why would that help?<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
<br>
- scadpaul<br>
<br>
(scad = Savannah College of Art &amp; Design, hopefully next year's new home) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uruney2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Runey2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/27/01 11:48:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Overcoming artist block and just plain STARTIN</span><hr size=1> Getting ideas going in rp can help with getting ideas going in drawing. And the least, you can draw silly doodles of everyone's characters getting mauled by the gamemaster's latest way-too-powerful monster-of-the-week. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uscadpaulg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>scadpaulg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/28/01 2:11:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Overcoming artist block and just plain STARTIN</span><hr size=1> I know this probably belonges in the critiques section, but if you would like to see some of my &quot;sight&quot; art, it's here: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.paulgreblick.com/oldsite/artgallery.htm">www.paulgreblick.com/olds...allery.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> .<br>
<br>
I don't have any &quot;creative&quot; art - it all sucks and I don't even know where to begin. (Except for the replies to my above msgs - Thanks, all!) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/udesignertonyc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Designer TonyC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/28/01 2:29:54 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Overcoming artist block and just plain STARTING.</span><hr size=1> hey! your pics are amazing ^_^, I can relate to you ^_^.  I can draw things I see pretty well, (have to practice shading) but I am staring to do figure drawing a lot now.  Heres my advice. actually, what I am doing right now, and it seems to work.<br>
<br>
Heres a little example.  Think of a fire hydrant.  Ok. draw it.  You probelly notice that you drew it the front view, ok.. now draw it 3/4 angle how about above angle? or a ant's view angle?  These are the things I think about when I draw. All the angles, and rotating the object in my mind  <br>
<br>
the thing is to think in MASS and 3-d. practice drawing something in any angle you can think of. once you can do that you can draw that from memory any time you want.<br>
<br>
pracitce figure drawing if thats is what I am assuming thats what you want to learn?  from your mind right?  well, to draw something from the mind you have to know what you are drawing right?  get a anatomy book, I recommend that you get &quot;Master Class in Figure Drawing&quot;  by Robert Hale.  Amazing book.  Study it, and keep drawing.  keep a book and keep drawing, and u can look back and see your progress.<br>
<br>
remmeber, &quot;First we draw what we see; then we draw what we know, finally we see what we know&quot;  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showMessage?topicID=1192.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showMessage?topicID=1183.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.emailToFriend?topicID=1182.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.threadControl?topicID=1182.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1182.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1182.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub25.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="polykarbonbbsfrm18">PK-BBS Rules and Regulations!<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm3">News and Updates<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm2">Photoshop and Art questions<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm4">General Manga Discussion<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm5">Japanese Language Help<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm23">art in progress<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm13">Black and White Art<option value="pol